   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4, \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\"kernelspec\": {\"display_name\": \"Python 3\", \"language\": \"python\", \"name\": \"python3\"}, \"language_info\": {\"name\": \"python\", \"version\": \"3.11.0\"}},\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"# Question Type Classification\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**NLP Project 10 of 100 · Beginner Text Classification**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This notebook builds a **multi-class classifier** that categorizes questions by type: factual, descriptive, entity-based, numeric, location, or person. We use the TREC question classification dataset and compare TF-IDF baselines against ModernBERT.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Models:** TF-IDF + MultinomialNB, LogReg, LinearSVC, SGD, RF, ModernBERT\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Metrics:** Accuracy, Macro-F1, Per-class Precision/Recall, Confusion Matrix\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Classify questions by their expected answer type\\n\", \"2. Use the TREC benchmark for question classification\\n\", \"3. Compare short-text classifiers (questions are typically 5-15 words)\\n\", \"4. Understand how question type aids downstream QA systems\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Given a question, classify it into one of 6 coarse types: **ABBR** (abbreviation), **DESC** (description), **ENTY** (entity), **HUM** (human), **LOC** (location), or **NUM** (numeric). This is a balanced multi-class problem.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Question type classification is a preprocessing step for QA systems\\n\", \"- Search engines use it to select appropriate answer strategies\\n\", \"- It teaches short-text classification where every word counts\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|----------|-------|\\n\", \"| Source | HuggingFace `CogComp/trec` |\\n\", \"| Classes | 6 coarse types (ABBR, DESC, ENTY, HUM, LOC, NUM) |\\n\", \"| Records | ~5,500 train + 500 test |\\n\", \"| Language | English |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"TREC Question Classification dataset (Li & Roth, 2002). Public academic benchmark.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Environment Setup\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"for pkg in ['pandas','numpy','matplotlib','seaborn','scikit-learn','datasets','transformers','accelerate']:\\n\", \"    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n\", \"    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\n\", \"print('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Imports\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"import os,json,warnings,random\\n\", \"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\n\", \"from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\n\", \"from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\\n\", \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression,SGDClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.calibration import CalibratedClassifierCV\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score,f1_score,classification_report,confusion_matrix\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\n\", \"sns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n\", \"%matplotlib inline\\n\", \"print('Imports loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Configuration / Constants\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"SEED=42; TFIDF_MAX=10000\\n\", \"MODEL_NAME='answerdotai/ModernBERT-base'; MAX_LEN=64; BS=32; EPOCHS=3; LR=2e-5\\n\", \"random.seed(SEED); np.random.seed(SEED)\\n\", \"SAVE_DIR=os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath('__file__'))\\n\", \"print(f'Seed: {SEED}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Download or Loading\\n\", \"\\n\", \"TREC has predefined train/test splits.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"from datasets import load_dataset\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    ds = load_dataset('CogComp/trec')\\n\", \"except Exception:\\n\", \"    ds = load_dataset('trec')\\n\", \"train_df = ds['train'].to_pandas()\\n\", \"test_df = ds['test'].to_pandas()\\n\", \"print(f'Train: {train_df.shape}, Test: {test_df.shape}')\\n\", \"print(f'Columns: {list(train_df.columns)}')\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Identify columns - TREC has 'text' (or 'question') and 'coarse_label' / 'fine_label'\\n\", \"text_col = 'text' if 'text' in train_df.columns else 'question' if 'question' in train_df.columns else train_df.columns[0]\\n\", \"label_col = 'coarse_label' if 'coarse_label' in train_df.columns else 'label-coarse' if 'label-coarse' in train_df.columns else train_df.columns[-1]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Get label names\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    LABEL_NAMES = ds['train'].features[label_col].names\\n\", \"except Exception:\\n\", \"    LABEL_NAMES = sorted(train_df[label_col].unique())\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f'Text: {text_col}, Label: {label_col}')\\n\", \"print(f'Classes: {LABEL_NAMES}')\\n\", \"print(f'Train distribution:\\\\n{train_df[label_col].value_counts()}')\\n\", \"train_df.head()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Data Validation Checks\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"print(f'Train missing: {train_df.isnull().sum().sum()}')\\n\", \"print(f'Test missing: {test_df.isnull().sum().sum()}')\\n\", \"print(f'Duplicates: {train_df.duplicated(subset=[text_col]).sum()}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"train_df['word_count'] = train_df[text_col].str.split().str.len()\\n\", \"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(14,5))\\n\", \"axes[0].hist(train_df['word_count'],bins=30,color='steelblue',edgecolor='black')\\n\", \"axes[0].set_title('Question Word Count')\\n\", \"vc = train_df[label_col].value_counts()\\n\", \"if isinstance(LABEL_NAMES,list) and len(LABEL_NAMES)>0:\\n\", \"    vc.index = [LABEL_NAMES[i] if isinstance(i,int) and i<len(LABEL_NAMES) else str(i) for i in vc.index]\\n\", \"vc.plot(kind='bar',ax=axes[1],color='steelblue',edgecolor='black')\\n\", \"axes[1].set_title('Question Type Distribution')\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'eda_distributions.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\\n\", \"print(f'Mean words: {train_df[\\\"word_count\\\"].mean():.1f}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"TREC coarse labels are moderately imbalanced. ENTY and DESC dominate; ABBR is rare.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"print(f'Proportions:\\\\n{(train_df[label_col].value_counts(normalize=True)*100).round(1)}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Train/Validation/Test Split Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Using predefined TREC train/test splits.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"X_train=train_df[text_col].values; y_train=train_df[label_col].values\\n\", \"X_test=test_df[text_col].values; y_test=test_df[label_col].values\\n\", \"print(f'Train: {len(X_train)}, Test: {len(X_test)}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Questions are short (avg 8-10 words). TF-IDF with bigrams captures question patterns like 'how many', 'what is', 'who'.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Feature Engineering\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"tfidf=TfidfVectorizer(max_features=TFIDF_MAX,sublinear_tf=True,ngram_range=(1,2))\\n\", \"X_tr=tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te=tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"print(f'TF-IDF: {X_tr.shape}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Baseline Model: TF-IDF + MultinomialNB\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"lbl_str = [str(l) for l in (LABEL_NAMES if isinstance(LABEL_NAMES,list) else sorted(np.unique(y_train)))]\\n\", \"bl=MultinomialNB(alpha=0.5); bl.fit(X_tr,y_train)\\n\", \"yp=bl.predict(X_te)\\n\", \"print(f'Baseline Macro-F1: {f1_score(y_test,yp,average=\\\"macro\\\"):.4f}')\\n\", \"print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=lbl_str))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Traditional ML Classifier Comparison\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> LazyPredict/FLAML not used for NLP.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"clfs={'MultinomialNB':MultinomialNB(alpha=0.5),\\n\", \"      'LogReg':LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000,random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced'),\\n\", \"      'LinearSVC':CalibratedClassifierCV(LinearSVC(max_iter=2000,random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced'),cv=3),\\n\", \"      'SGD':CalibratedClassifierCV(SGDClassifier(loss='hinge',random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced',max_iter=1000),cv=3),\\n\", \"      'RF':RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=300,random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced',n_jobs=-1)}\\n\", \"results=[]; trained_models={}\\n\", \"for name,clf in clfs.items():\\n\", \"    clf.fit(X_tr,y_train); yp=clf.predict(X_te)\\n\", \"    r={'Model':name,'Accuracy':accuracy_score(y_test,yp),'Macro_F1':f1_score(y_test,yp,average='macro')}\\n\", \"    results.append(r); trained_models[name]=(clf,yp)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"{name:15s} | Acc={r['Accuracy']:.4f} | Macro-F1={r['Macro_F1']:.4f}\\\")\\n\", \"pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values('Macro_F1',ascending=False)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Why FLAML Is Not Used Here\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> Not applicable for NLP.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Transformer Approach: ModernBERT Fine-Tuning\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"tr_res=None; y_pred_t=None\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    import torch\\n\", \"    from transformers import AutoTokenizer,AutoModelForSequenceClassification,Trainer,TrainingArguments\\n\", \"    from datasets import Dataset\\n\", \"    dev='cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'; torch.manual_seed(SEED)\\n\", \"    num_labels = len(set(y_train))\\n\", \"    td=pd.DataFrame({'text':X_train,'label':y_train.astype(int) if y_train.dtype!=object else y_train})\\n\", \"    tds=Dataset.from_pandas(td); eds=Dataset.from_pandas(pd.DataFrame({'text':X_test,'label':y_test.astype(int) if y_test.dtype!=object else y_test}))\\n\", \"    tok=AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\\n\", \"    def tf(ex): return tok(ex['text'],truncation=True,padding='max_length',max_length=MAX_LEN)\\n\", \"    tds=tds.map(tf,batched=True); eds=eds.map(tf,batched=True)\\n\", \"    tds.set_format('torch',columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\", \"    eds.set_format('torch',columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\", \"    m=AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME,num_labels=num_labels).to(dev)\\n\", \"    a=TrainingArguments(output_dir='./out',num_train_epochs=EPOCHS,per_device_train_batch_size=BS,\\n\", \"        per_device_eval_batch_size=BS*2,warmup_ratio=0.1,weight_decay=0.01,learning_rate=LR,\\n\", \"        eval_strategy='epoch',save_strategy='no',logging_steps=50,report_to='none',seed=SEED,fp16=torch.cuda.is_available())\\n\", \"    def cm(ep): p=np.argmax(ep.predictions,axis=1); return {'accuracy':accuracy_score(ep.label_ids,p),'macro_f1':f1_score(ep.label_ids,p,average='macro')}\\n\", \"    t=Trainer(model=m,args=a,train_dataset=tds,eval_dataset=eds,compute_metrics=cm)\\n\", \"    t.train(); po=t.predict(eds); y_pred_t=np.argmax(po.predictions,axis=1)\\n\", \"    tr_res={'Model':'ModernBERT','Accuracy':accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred_t),'Macro_F1':f1_score(y_test,y_pred_t,average='macro')}\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"ModernBERT Macro-F1={tr_res['Macro_F1']:.4f}\\\")\\n\", \"    del m,t; torch.cuda.empty_cache() if torch.cuda.is_available() else None\\n\", \"except Exception as e: print(f'Transformer skipped: {e}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Top 3 Model Selection\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"ar=results.copy()\\n\", \"if tr_res: ar.append(tr_res)\\n\", \"adf=pd.DataFrame(ar).sort_values('Macro_F1',ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"print(adf.to_string(index=False,float_format='{:.4f}'.format))\\n\", \"top3=adf.head(3)['Model'].tolist(); print(f'Top 3: {top3}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"t3d={}\\n\", \"for n in top3:\\n\", \"    if n in trained_models: t3d[n]=trained_models[n][1]\\n\", \"    elif n=='ModernBERT' and y_pred_t is not None: t3d[n]=y_pred_t\\n\", \"nc=len(t3d)\\n\", \"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,nc,figsize=(6*nc,5))\\n\", \"if nc==1: axes=[axes]\\n\", \"for i,(n,yp) in enumerate(t3d.items()):\\n\", \"    sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test,yp),annot=True,fmt='d',cmap='Blues',\\n\", \"                xticklabels=lbl_str,yticklabels=lbl_str,ax=axes[i])\\n\", \"    axes[i].set_title(n)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'confusion_matrices.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\\n\", \"for n,yp in t3d.items(): print(f'\\\\n{n}'); print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=lbl_str))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Error Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"bp=t3d[top3[0]]\\n\", \"edf=pd.DataFrame({'text':X_test,'true':y_test,'pred':bp})\\n\", \"errs=edf[edf['true']!=edf['pred']]\\n\", \"print(f'Errors: {len(errs)}/{len(edf)} ({len(errs)/len(edf)*100:.1f}%)')\\n\", \"for _,r in errs.head(5).iterrows():\\n\", \"    tl = lbl_str[r['true']] if isinstance(r['true'],int) else str(r['true'])\\n\", \"    pl = lbl_str[r['pred']] if isinstance(r['pred'],int) else str(r['pred'])\\n\", \"    print(f'  True: {tl} | Pred: {pl} | Q: {r[\\\"text\\\"]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Question types are largely signaled by interrogative words ('who'→HUM, 'where'→LOC, 'how many'→NUM).\\n\", \"2. ENTY is the hardest class because it covers diverse entity types.\\n\", \"3. Short questions mean every word matters — TF-IDF bigrams capture key patterns.\\n\", \"4. This classification step improves downstream QA answer extraction.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. 6 coarse types miss subtleties. 2. Factoid questions only. 3. English only.\\n\", \"4. Real QA systems need 50+ fine-grained types.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## How to Improve\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Use 50-class fine-grained TREC labels. 2. Add question pattern features.\\n\", \"3. Combine with answer extraction for end-to-end QA.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Ultra-low latency needed (pre-QA step). TF-IDF is ideal.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Ignoring the ABBR class (very rare). 2. Not using interrogative word features.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Use fine-grained TREC labels (50 classes). 2. Add hand-crafted features for question words.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Question type classification is short-text multi-class NLP.\\n\", \"2. Interrogative words are the strongest features.\\n\", \"3. TF-IDF + LinearSVC achieves >85% accuracy on TREC.\\n\", \"4. ModernBERT provides improvement on ambiguous questions.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"fm={'project':'Question Type Classification','task':'multi_class_text_classification',\\n\", \"    'dataset':'CogComp/trec','models':{}}\\n\", \"for r in ar: fm['models'][r['Model']]={k:round(v,4) if isinstance(v,float) else v for k,v in r.items() if k!='Model'}\\n\", \"mp=os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'metrics.json')\\n\", \"with open(mp,'w') as f: json.dump(fm,f,indent=2)\\n\", \"print(f'Saved: {mp}'); print(json.dumps(fm,indent=2))\"]}\n",
    " ]\n",
    "}\n"
   ],
   "id": "c81da0b22d373698"
  }
